# Module Structure Rules

## Directory Organization
- Each module must have exactly these subdirectories: controller/, internal/, ui/
- Place REST API endpoints only in controller/ subdirectory
- Place Entity, Service, Repository, and DTOs only in internal/ subdirectory  
- Place Vaadin views and custom components only in ui/ subdirectory
- Create MyModuleFacade.java at module root level as public API
- Include package-info.java with @Module annotation and documentation

## Module Boundaries
- Only MyModuleFacade.java should be public API for other modules
- Internal package classes must not be accessed from other modules
- All inter-module communication through facades or events only
- Never import from other modules' internal packages

## File Naming Conventions
- Facade classes: [ModuleName]Facade.java
- Controllers: [ModuleName]Controller.java  
- Services: [ModuleName]ModuleService.java (internal only)
- Entities: [DomainName].java
- Repositories: [DomainName]Repository.java
- Views: [ModuleName]View.java
- Components: [ComponentName]Component.java

